```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.fbgroupmarketingscri">

    <!-- 
        This manifest file defines the application configuration for 
        "fb group marketing script - Android Automation Tool". It includes 
        necessary permissions, component registration, and other configurations 
        to ensure the proper functioning of social media automation features.
    -->

    <!-- 
        This powerful permission enables the application to access the internet, 
        allowing for seamless communication with social media platforms for 
        automated operations and content management.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    
    <!-- 
        This comprehensive capability allows the application to write to 
        external storage, enabling the saving of generated content, logs, 
        and other important files necessary for automation tasks.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    
    <!-- 
        This flexible configuration option provides read access to 
        external storage, essential for retrieving any required files 
        for automation processes, ensuring smooth operations.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="fb group marketing script - Android Automation Tool"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.DayNight">

        <!-- 
            The MainActivity serves as the entry point for the application, 
            providing users with an interface to configure and control the 
            automation features for social media management.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            The AutomationService runs in the background, enabling 24/7 automated 
            operations without user intervention. It handles all scheduled tasks 
            and content management activities for social media platforms.
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:enabled="true"
            android:exported="false" />

    </application>

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Features:

- **Permissions**: 
   - The **INTERNET** permission allows the application to connect to online services, which is essential for managing social media interactions.
   - The **WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE** and **READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE** permissions enable the application to save and read files, which supports content management and automation tasks.

- **Components**:
   - **MainActivity** acts as the user interface for interacting with the automation tool, allowing users to set up and manage their social media activities effectively.
   - **AutomationService** is a background service that provides continuous operation for scheduled tasks, ensuring that user-defined automation runs smoothly without delays.

This configuration ensures that MadHub's powerful automation capabilities are accessible, enhancing the user's experience with efficient social media management.
